<P><HI>T. D.</HI> Another example (as thou callest it) as <HI>Remarkable</HI> as this, Thou sayest was in <HI>Christ-Church,</HI> Octob. 6. 1659. where on <HI>a Day of publique Thanks-giving</HI> the Parliament, L. Major, Aldermen, Common Councel, and Officers of the Army <HI>being met together to hear</HI> Dr. Homes &amp; Mr. Caryl, <HI>appointed by the Parliament to preach before them; two Qua. made a great di|sturbance in the very presence of Authority.</HI></P>
