rds them under it, as well while we are speaking, as we are moved of the Lord, in our own allowed meetings, as in theirs: witness their leading a <HI>Bear</HI> through the place, where the <HI>Qua.</HI> were Preaching pub|lickly at <HI>Hith</HI>: and also the <HI>rudeness</HI> of some of those that are under thy own <HI>Tuition T.D.</HI> at <HI>Sandwich,</HI> and belonging to the <HI>Flock</HI> thou there feedest, or rather feedest on; who when <HI>G. F. E. B.</HI> my self and many others were publickly met in quiet in a place of our friends procuring, shrew Stones and <HI>Gunpowder squibs</HI> that fired among us, not so as to move us to cry out to the <HI>Rulers</HI> of <HI>Disturbance,</HI> yet so as to give good occasion
