<P>Their 29th from <HI>Deut.</HI> 4.8. <HI>Psal.</HI> 147.19.20. <HI>Rom.</HI> 3.1.2. is thus: <HI>What advantage then hath the Ierk, and what pr<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">fit is there in Circumcision, if (each</HI> Gentile <HI>had a Light within him, as a sufficient guide in the things of God,</HI> as the <HI>Qua.</HI> teach) <HI>then they had known Gods Statutes and Iudgements Gods Oracles had been committed to them as well as to the Iews, they had had, as righteous Statutes, and been as wise a Nation as they: But these consequents are false, and contrary to the Texts.</HI></P>
